query: Can you show me the syllabus for CMPSC 311 (SP25)?

document.title: Syllabus for CMPSC 311 (SP25)
document.content: Instructor Information Dr. John Smith Professor Department of Computer Science and Engineering Email: jds123@psu.edu Teaching Assistants • Ashwin Senthil Arumugam • Neeraj Karamchandani Office Hours Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Dr. John Smith Location: W109F Westgate Building 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM 9:00 AM - 10:00 AM Ashwin Senthil Arumugam Location: 300W building 2:00 PM - 3:00 PM 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM Neeraj Karamchandani Location: Zoom Online 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM Course Objectives: This course explores intro sys prog concepts and methodologies. Students will gain hands-on experience through lectures, programming assignments, and projects. Grading Activity Percentage Course Projects 50% Midterm Exams 30% Final Exam 20% Academic Integrity Statement The course projects are to be carried out individually. Students are explicitly not allowed to share information, source code, or even discuss the contents of the projects. Any violation of this policy will be considered cheating and will result in the student receiving an 'F' grade for the project. Lateness Policy Lab assignments are assessed a 10% per day late penalty, up to a maximum of three days after which a zero grade will be given.
